Description: The geotools package is an R library designed to simplify the
    management, analysis, and processing of space-time data. In particular,
    it provides a comprehensive set of modules that enable the computation of
    statistics for space-time variables (e.g., meteorological and air quality
    data) whose values are available on different spatial heterogeneous grids at
    the polygonal scale (e.g., municipal or regional).
